    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      96.02,
      361.95,
      526.86,
      376.01
    ],
    "text": "(iii) The period of time within which an appeal should be preferred must be",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial-ItalicMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      383.07,
      526.72,
      397.13
    ],
    "text": "calculated from the date on which the reasons are given. The",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      404.21,
      526.75,
      418.27
    ],
    "text": "conviction/sentence was given on 22.7.98. The Petition of Appeal was",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      425.33,
      447.34,
      439.39
    ],
    "text": "lodged on 17.9.1999. The appeal is therefore out of time.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      96.02,
      446.45,
      526.8,
      460.51
    ],
    "text": "(iv) An application in Revision should not be entertained save in exceptional",
    "fonts": [
      "Arial-ItalicMT",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      467.57,
      526.81,
      481.63
    ],
    "text": "circumstances. When considering this issue court must necessarily have",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      488.69,
      526.68,
      502.75
    ],
    "text": "regard to the contumacious conduct of the accused in jumping bail and",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      509.93,
      526.91,
      523.99
    ],
    "text": "thereafter his conduct in a manner to circumvent and subvert the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      531.05,
      526.8,
      545.11
    ],
    "text": "process of the law and judicial institutions. In addition, the party should",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.62,
      552.17,
      393.82,
      566.23
    ],
    "text": "come before Court without unreasonable delay.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      96.02,
      583.28,
      527.28,
      597.28
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Padmasiri v Attorney General 2012(1) SLR 24, it was held:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      614.48,
      526.84,
      628.54
    ],
    "text": "\u201c\u2026.if we are to allow this application it would amount to condescending",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      635.6,
      526.8,
      649.66
    ],
    "text": "or, the court lending its hands to a person who is guilty of contumacious",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      656.72,
      526.72,
      670.78
    ],
    "text": "conduct and thereby assisting him. Therefore, we hold that the petition",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      114.02,
      677.84,
      440.02,
      691.9
    ],
    "text": "of appeal is not properly constituted and is out of time.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      260.69,
      35.25,
      342.73,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0011/2023",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "5 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      88.32,
      527.52,
      102.32
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Opatha Mudiyanselage Nimal Perera v Attorney-General",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      109.56,
      282.79,
      123.62
    ],
    "text": "[2002] 3 SLR 101 it was held that:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      140.64,
      526.68,
      154.7
    ],
    "text": "\"These matters must be considered in limine before the Court decides to",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      161.76,
      526.9,
      175.82
    ],
    "text": "hear the accused-petitioner on the merits of his application. Before he could",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      182.88,
      526.68,
      196.94
    ],
    "text": "pass the gateway to relief his aforesaid contumacious conduct and his",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      204.0,
      526.91,
      218.06
    ],
    "text": "unreasonable and undue delay in filing the application must be considered",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      225.12,
      526.68,
      239.18
    ],
    "text": "and determination made upon those matters before he is heard on the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      246.39,
      249.89,
      260.45
    ],
    "text": "merits of the application.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      277.47,
      527.28,
      291.47
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Attorney General v Podisingho 51 NLR 385, it was held that:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      308.55,
      526.69,
      322.61
    ],
    "text": "\u201cthe powers of revision of the Supreme Court are wide enough to embrace",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      329.67,
      526.66,
      343.73
    ],
    "text": "a case where an appeal lay but was not taken. In such a case, however,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      350.79,
      526.68,
      364.85
    ],
    "text": "an application in revision should not be entertained save in exceptional",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      372.03,
      526.88,
      386.09
    ],
    "text": "circumstances, such as, (a) where there has been a miscarriage of justice,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      393.15,
      526.82,
      407.21
    ],
    "text": "(6) where a strong case for the interference of the Supreme Court has been",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      414.29,
      526.63,
      428.35
    ],
    "text": "made out by the petitioner, or (c) where the applicant was unaware of the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      435.41,
      289.75,
      449.47
    ],
    "text": "order made by the Court of trial\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      466.49,
      524.28,
      480.49
    ],
    "text": "In the case of Ediriweera v Attorney-General (2006 1 SLR 25) it was held:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      497.69,
      526.67,
      511.75
    ],
    "text": "\u201cIf the High Court Judge's order is correct, that there are no exceptional",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      518.81,
      526.69,
      532.87
    ],
    "text": "circumstances the order cannot be revised. Revisionary powers should be",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      539.93,
      526.75,
      553.99
    ],
    "text": "exercised where a miscarriage of justice has occurred due to a",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      561.08,
      526.94,
      575.14
    ],
    "text": "fundamental rule of procedure being violated, but only when a strong case",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      582.2,
      440.98,
      596.26
    ],
    "text": "is made out amounting to a positive miscarriage of justice.\"",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      613.28,
      527.04,
      627.28
    ],
    "text": "In this case as stated earlier, the Appellant lodged an appeal against the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      634.4,
      527.0,
      648.4
    ],
    "text": "judgment. Considering the provisions of law, his appeal is out of time. He",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      655.52,
      527.03,
      669.52
    ],
    "text": "could not succeed in the inquiry held under Section 241(3) of the Code of",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      676.76,
      527.21,
      690.76
    ],
    "text": "Criminal Procedure Act. Had he been successful in the inquiry he could have",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      697.88,
      527.16,
      711.94
    ],
    "text": "had the benefit of a trial in de-novo. In this case, the learned High Court",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      719.0,
      527.18,
      733.0
    ],
    "text": "Judge had considered the evidence presented by both parties to arrive at his",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      260.69,
      35.25,
      342.73,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0011/2023",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "6 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      88.32,
      527.28,
      102.32
    ],
    "text": "decision. He has properly analysed the evidence given by both sides in his",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      109.56,
      141.38,
      123.56
    ],
    "text": "judgment.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      140.64,
      474.1,
      154.64
    ],
    "text": "Therefore, I dismiss the Appeal of the Appellant as it is out of time.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
